entry.def: If someone gatecrashes a party or other social event, they go to it, even though they have not been invited.

example.ex: Scores of people tried desperately to gatecrash the party...
example.tran: 很多不速之客拼命想要挤进这个聚会。

example.ex: He had gatecrashed but he was with other people we knew and there was no problem.
example.tran: 他不请自来，但他是跟我们认识的人同行，因此也没有什么关系。

means.word_mean: 1. someone who gets in (to a party) without an invitation or without paying
